@Steve L

As a solver who only looks at the clock out of sheer curiosity after I'm done and engages the puzzle like I'm out for a leisurely walk or motorcycle ride, can you splain me the congruity of "Very Hard" and "Median Solve Time 24:55?"

How can a very hard Sunday take 25 minutes to solve?

@Matt

Think of the median solve time as a par in golf.  The weekend duffer won't break it most of the time, but it's still the standard. And it still serves it purpose to give an idea about level of difficulty.

Plus, what John said.

